reviews.text: It open to the public no charge to come and walk around. Buy a bag of food for a dollar to feed the mountain goats and the lama. Donkeys and some other animals. Small but entertaining. Paddle boats forr rent also

It is a pretty neat place they have a petting zoo there and they also have food where you can feed the animals they have a dairy farm. They specialize in making asadero cheese it is delicious. They also have a store in case if you want to buy drinks and snacks to picnic there. My family like that the kids had a lot of fun and there was very relaxing I really recommend this place for a family outing

What a great place to bring the family.  The handmade cheeses are unreal...Mmmmm. The petting zoo for the kids is a nice attraction but the real reason to come here is the Asadero Cheese. Magnificent!

Tasty cheese with a wonderful family story behind it spanning multiple generations of locally produced dairy products. Wonderful local secret tucked away in El Paso's Eastern suburbs, waiting for cheese lovers to discover.

Also love the collection of comical signs collected by the owners wife (some of which are pictured).

Free parking lot out the front.
Wow. Super gem to visit. Great cheese at good prices. And a free zoo for the family to see, including several more exotic animals. Peaceful location. I recommend it.

Excellent University! You get what you put into it. Provides students with great opportunities to better themselves in their careers. Can’t beat the price. School has gone through a lot of remodeling and new construction making it innovative and modern looking. ⛏😊👨🏻‍🎓👩🏻‍🎓

Utep is a very nice school.
International office is kinda lost some of them r just students and they do not know all the work so when u get lost with them just tell them u wanna talk with an advisor or supervisor I am not sure which one is it. Parking is awful issue if u don’t buy the permit in May u will suffer.
If you are a sophomore in IE and u wanna register IE classes you will have a problem because all the classes are almost full.

UTEP Is a nice university in the south of the US near to the border with Mexico. Used to harbor people from almost everywhere, now has many Mexican students that are coming to pursue their dream. I feel happy for them, but definitely UTEP's past population diversity made it phenomenal for international students to meet each other.

This is a great university. Despite bad raps it may get, the actual education you get (if you want to learn and better yourself, that is) is not reflective of the "statistics." As far as my personal experience goes (got a BBA in accounting and finance) the university's ranking nationally or admittance rate has not affected me in the least. I am currently pursuing a law degree in Ohio and I'm able to compete with anyone from "top tier" schools like Ohio State without an issue. Ultimately, it is up to you to make use of whatever resources you have, and the tools UTEP provides are indeed valuable.

I don't recommend this university. Only come to this university if you have to, and the universities 99% acceptance rate demonstrates this. The University is full of people that didn't get into other universities or that they have to attend this one. The University has full of professors that didn't get accepted to teach (or do research) at better universities. And of course you have exceptions but it seems to be more of a rule than exception. So not only do you have the worst students, you have the worst professors. Not a great combination in my opinion. Sounds like a blast. Oh yeah whether you have options or not, it doesn't change the facts that the university ranks at the end of the list in the country.
The gardens were beautiful.  The prettiest spot in El Paso.  The museum was interesting, and the short term exhibits were well done.
Great native plant examples on display. Beautiful
Had the opportunity to spend an afternoon here for a teacher professional development. The surroundings were beautiful and quite stimulating. Definitely worth the trip from Fort Worth.
Small museum inside the UTEP campus that has geological and fossil displays. Also has some traditional clothing on display early natives wore.
Great exhibits and service

We love going to the shows and we have not had a bad dinner yet. My husband loves the coffee. I just wish they would allow us to purchase tickets at the same time as alumni. It's hard sometimes to find the seats we like.  When you have back and neck issues,  it makes a huge difference where you sit.
Awesome show with my grandma. Service is on point. Food could be better. Cast was awesome for Newsies.
Good food and great entertainment.  Every play we have seen has been outstanding 🙌.
Enjoyed the show. The nachos needed more cheese.  My bottom chips had no cheese..
Wonderful performance. The food was ...me. I w9uld expect better food for what we paid for it.  The seating is a bit too cramped especially when watching the performance.

I give it 5 stars because there I use their parking lot to teach my children and friends how to drive a stick shift car and also taught my wife how to drive a motorcycle, since they have the motorcycle course there, I was able to use it to teach her. I don't know what is going to happen to the actual stadium, but it seems like it is just going to waste, since it is rarely used.
Great place for a motor cycle class, lines are painted on the parking lot, great place to improve skill as a rider
Shouldn't destroy it . Really nice music under the stars.. I like it . First time but not the last
Cohen may be losing its spunk because of downtown stadium. But it still has charm and great events for family and friends.
Cohen stadium was much more fun

Food is good and reasonably priced. Coffee is fine.  But it's definitely better as a dry season venue if you are having lunch. Can be pretty hot during the day so make sure you snag a spot with a fan.
Nice, helpful staff. Decent beer. Okay food. Reasonable prices.

Best meal I had in Darwin. I thought ok it's a pub meal will likely be rather average but wow did they impress. I had the pork ribs with fries and coleslaw, amazing. Fast service and friendly staff. Order and bar and collect.
staff were very nice and friendly. Food was top quality, would highly recommend! Convenient location, thanks guys!

Very laid back. But good for s Saturday night.
Well done guys

One of the best Steak House joints ever! Great atmosphere with superb service.  Very clean and awesome Western setting off course you are in the West!! This is one of those places, if you don't go then why did you go to Texas?  You'll spend some cash but never forget it.  It has been 4 weeks since I been there and I still talk about it!

I brought my aunt and my cousin because this is her "go to" place and a little bit of pampering was in order. My aunt absolutely loves the Cole slaw with pineapple and it became an instant favorite of mine. A meal for 3 adults and 1 child came out to $140 so this place is not cheap by any means.  The frozen cheesecake was great and the pecan pie was mouthwatering.  I would definitely come back. 

The only downside was that our waitstaff was a little inattentive.

Get to room the land seeing the different animals then up to the restaurant for excellent meal with great service. Exploring in the restaurant is awesome as well with the many photos of films shot there. Excellent family experience. Bit pricey but well worth it.

The best steak you can ever eat!! With some mushrooms on side and an order of some huge shrimp!!! Man makes me want to go right now!! Beautiful view and little zoo they have. It is super fun to go walk around enjoy outside with the animals and nice sights and then a great meal!!

The BEST STEAK ever!!!
We hosted an event with over 80 in attendance the food was excellent and the room was perfect. 
The entire staff was friendly and fun. 
The best thing besides the steak was the price, what a great deal and the ambience and sunset was breathtaking to say the least

My daughter in-laws brother had his wedding reception there and they had like a buffet set up it was around 15 people she said everything was perfect and bride and groom were satisfied it is not cheap but it is quality food I went over 20 years ago and I never forgot the lamb chop I had if you want a day to remember and great food this is the top. Cafe Central has a nice atmosphere and very good live music. The food is very good as same as the wine. The service is very good and the place is expensive.

This review actually just showed up for the wrong restaurant. This is the correct restaurant. Im sitting. 2 blocks from our southern border. "Best restaurant in town" a fellow flyer told me. Fully expecting Mexican food I was surprised and delighted to enjoy incredibly delicious Italian Food! Valet parking and beautiful decor combined with a very well trained staff provided a fabulous, white table cloth style dining experience. They feature an extensive wine list. My lobster ravioli was so good I thought about it for hours. My friends commented that their meals were incredible as well. Yes,El Paso features some great Mexican restaurants. But, if you love Italian food, this us the place. First class all the way;

Good service. Good food. Average entree priced about $30.
We were seated where cold air would blast us every time door was opened and it was opened frequently. Plenty of seating available. Would have been nice to have been seated out of the cold blast.

This place is amazing!  Now, by no means am I made out of money nor do I make a lot of money.  But the staff here treats everyone with 5 star service.  From the moment you walk in, as they open the door you're welcomed by modern decor and soft lighting setting the mood for a romantic evening.  You are warmly greeted by the front staff and they take your coat.  The tables look lovely with a cream white table cloths, two large wine glasses and silverware methodically laid out for you.  The wait staff was awesome working as a team to provide you the type of service you usually get at fancy restaurants in Beverly Hills, but here in El Paso.  I never had to wait for a drink or a refill.  The food was delicious and it came out promptly.  Yeah, it is a little pricey, but you definitely get more than what you paid for here.  It was worth every dollar and I will definitely be coming back again.
Food is always delicious and the service is great!! The staff is friendly and takes pride in remembering their customers. Love this place for lunch, dinner and special occasions.

We liked Forti's dining experience. It was much more stylish than your typical Mexican restaurant. Food was fantastic and came with notable portion size. The only thing that dropped it a star was the tiny wine pours. Looked like a 1/3 a glass in there.
The food was excellent, service was awesome. Can't go wrong coming here to eat. Prices are good. Margaritas are large and strong, you will love them. Excellent atmosphere,  and beautiful restaurant..

Great food, the cheese red enchiladas were amazing! Definitely should try them... The place is beautiful, the service is excellent, fair price. The day I was there, they had a folklore dance going on.. It was a great experience, everyone seemed to enjoy it.... Highly recommend

We decided to bring family from out of town here because the food is notoriously delicious. Nothing could’ve prepared us for the experience. Customer service was bad and there wasn’t a lot of tables to wait on. Flautas, were absolutely horrible. They weren’t made with shredded beef and honestly I don’t know what was in them, tasted unlike anything I've ever had. Safe to say we won’t be back, ever.
I LOVE the set up here, VERY authentic. Reminds me of an hacienda type home.  The food is good also. I wish the salsa(Chile) was a bit more spicy though. Other than that, pretty chilled place to be.
